text: 🍲Lẩu Đuôi Bò🐂 #Unihub #UnihubTeam #Food #torofoodie #Foodies Sẽ là một thiếu sót to lớn nếu nói đến thịt bò mà quên mất những món từ Đuôi Bò. Nếu các phần thịt khác của bò đã quá phổ biến và làm bạn dễ ngán thì đuôi bò sẽ là một lựa chọn "đổi gió" tuyệt vời.  Là một loại lẩu dễ ăn , chứa nhiều dinh dưỡng , nước lẩu thanh ngọt đậm đà , lượng thịt ở phần đuôi không quá nhiều vì vậy rất đỡ ngán , cùng với đó phần da và sụn ở đuôi bò ăn lại ngọt bùi , lạ miệng rất kích thích khẩu vị.  Rau nêm trong lẩu bò thường lá hành lá và tía tô. Ngoài ra, bạn còn có thể nấu lẩu cùng với củ khoai môn, củ sen, nấm rơm, nấm hương. Khi thưởng thức, bạn có thể nhúng rau cải xanh, cải ngọt, tần ô, rau má, mồng tơi.

text: On August 18, 2012, Nancy Howard spent her day doing church activities in Carrollton, Texas. Later that day, a young man assaulted her in her garage, demanding her purse.   In a moment of confusion, she handed him her food bag instead. Frustrated, he shot her in the face, fleeing with her purse and leaving her seriously injured.  By some miracle she not only survived, but managed to drag herself into her house and call an ambulance.   The bullet destroyed Nancy’s eye and became lodged in her lung, leaving her in coma for days after the horrific ordeal.  Nancy's husband, Frank Howard, appeared to lead a normal life with her, involved in church and community. Unbeknownst to Nancy, Frank was having an affair with Suzanne Leontieff and frequently travelled under the guise of business.    As police began to delve deeper into their investigation they discovered that it was actually Frank who orchestrated the shooting. Frank hired Billie Earl Johnson and planned his wife’s murder to look like a robbery gone wrong.   Frank was arrested and eventually sentenced to life in prison for the heinous crime. Despite the fact he tried to kill her, Nancy said she forgave Frank.

But then pasteurization was instituted by the Rockefellers in the 1920’s, forcing out local small farmers who could not pay for the expensive pasteurization equipment.  Today’s milk is accused of causing everything from allergies to cancer, but when people could buy real raw milk, these diseases were rare.  Today science shows that pasteurization destroys enzymes, denatures anti-microbial and immune-stimulating components, diminishes nutrient availability, denatures fragile milk proteins, destroys vitamins C, B6 and B12, kills beneficial bacteria, promotes pathogens and is associated with allergies, increased tooth decay, colic in infants, growth and behavior problems in children, osteoporosis, arthritis and heart disease.  Calves fed pasteurized milk do poorly and often die before maturity.  Raw milk sours naturally but pasteurized milk turns putrid.  So if the government really cares about the health of their citizens, why do they continue to make it harder & harder for people to find real, natural & healthy foods?  Why are they doing nothing about the processed junk foods that are wreaking insane amounts of havoc on the world?  Have they been corrupted by lobbyists from the food & pharma industry, who profit from sick people?  Are people with reduced nutrient availability easier to control?  Many such questions can be asked by those who dare to utter them.  One thing is for sure.. When it comes to health in the modern world, people HAVE to start making their own decisions, because the government no longer has our best interest at heart..   If it ever had. text: A 4000 year-old bowl of noodles unearthed in China is the earliest example ever found of one of the world's most popular foods. It also suggests an Asian not Italian origin for the staple dish.  The beautifully preserved, long, thin yellow noodles were found inside an overturned sealed bowl at the Lajia archaeological site in northwestern China. The bowl was buried under 3m of sediment.  Scientists determined noodles were made from two kinds of millet, a grain indigenous to China and widely cultivated there 7000 years ago. Modern North American and European noodles are usually made with wheat.  - Subscribe for Detailed Post -  #archaeohistories

text: This #disabled #bipolar man living in #poverty is ending 2023 -$300 and that means I can in no way afford life. Please Help me raise $1200, which will allow me to get current and get #food to eat, and pay rent.  I live in constant physical pain, as all over full body constantly hurting pain. Over the past few years as I get older it is getting much worse, and my bed desperately needs a new mattress, but this #disabled #bipolar man lives in #poverty and cant afford to replace it, but the past few months I have gotten very little sleep, one because my #anxiety has been getting worse, but also because laying down on my sunken mattress really makes my pain worse, and no I dont have a chair to sleep in. In the first spot on my #amazonwishlist is a mattress will you all help me obtain it? https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/1MUVXODQ665D0?ref_=wl_share  someone please help ease some of my pain today.  At what point do you just give up? How long do you suffer and struggle, as you cry out for help that never comes?  How do you deal with being so overwhelmed, you cant even think straight? Where do you start, when everything is in ruins?  From being in extreme debt, to constantly struggling to have enough if any food to eat, to constantly worrying about your living situation, because time changes what you had planed, not having the support you really need, and being left to feel that the victim card only makes you look weak, but in reality you really are weak, your strength, will and resolve are gone, hope burned out so long ago you don’t even remember ever having any.  Emotions don’t change just because suddenly relief may come, but the emotions from suffering and struggling until it does is nearly unbearable.  Talking won’t help, because your not in my shoes, you don’t see with my eyes, and you cant really understand how bad it all is. From the outside it may look sad, maybe a little off course, but its never that bad. From the inside its so dark black would be light. I get you don’t think money will change things for me. But raising the money I need, will enable me to eat, which will give me strength to face the day, money will allow me to pay off my bills, which will allow me to breath without a weight on my chest, money will allow me to obtain property, build a home, that can be mine forever, giving me peace and security, see money right now, will help me get to where I can finally focus on fixing the rest of me.  I have been begging and begging, Please Help Me, but no one is listening, and no is caring.  I am currently -$$$ in my bank account, I have not enough food to eat every day this month, I am over $6,000 in debt, today $10,000 will let me pay everything and to buy food for the next 30 days, $3-5million will let me buy property to build my forever home, and if I raise only $3million, and Say I spend $1.5 to buy property, build a forever home, fill it with all you need to live, Id still have around $1.5million in the bank, which works out to around $37,000 a year for the next 40 years, allowing me to cover taxes, utilities, maintenance, and normal life expenses, $37,000 a year is a great deal more than my current $12,000 a year, so yes money will and can help me, it can truly change my life.  I beg of you once more, PLEASE HELP ME Today, Please give Hope and Life via https://paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=GB6CYVMK53E4Y Thank You, a desperate and broken man.  I know that times are tough for everyone right now, but even a small #donation can make a big difference in my life. Your support will help me to pay for basic necessities like #food, #clothing, and #shelter. It will also help me to cover the cost of #transportation to and from important appointments, such as shopping for food and #groceries and what ever else may arise that requires me to get out and about. Living with bipolar disorder is challenging, but it doesn't have to define me. I am a determined and hardworking individual, and I am committed to living a fulfilling life. With your support, I can achieve my goals some of which you can read via https://2ndshot.photos/hope and reach my full potential. Here are some specific ways that your donation can help me: Pay for food and clothing: As a disabled bipolar man living in poverty, I often struggle to afford basic necessities. Your donation would help me to ensure that I have enough to eat and wear. Cover the cost of transportation: I need to be able to get to and from important appointments, such as shopping for food and groceries. Your donation would help me to cover the cost of transportation, so that I don't have to worry about how I'm going to get around. Help me to find and maintain #housing: Having a safe and stable place to live is essential for my well-being. Your donation would help me to maintain housing, so that I can focus on my #recovery and my goals for the future. I am grateful for any support that you can offer. Even a small donation given with love via #Paypal https://paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=GB6CYVMK53E4Y can make a big difference in my life. Thank you for your consideration.  You can give with love via,  #Venmo https://venmo.com/code?user_id=328092060c1690112927&created=1654260352 or via #Paypal https://paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=GB6CYVMK53E4Y You can purchase my collection of Manic Sounds, an expressive collection of my #soundscapes via https://2ndshot.photos/downloads/manic-sounds/ you can purchase some of my digital art suitable for your desktop wallpaper, via https://2ndshot.photos/downloads/a-collection-of-25-creative-visual-digital-art-works/ you can buy some of my printed odd ball art work via https://www.redbubble.com/people/woctxphotog/explore?asc=u #disabled #bipolar man today, Please and Thank You.  Sincerely, Philip

text: It is that time of the year on Uganda’s social calendar when there is the ba-summer (Ugandans working abroad) invasion. They are known for causing “inflation” in town because of too much spending on expensive drinks and food. Their expenditure also spreads to driving around luxurious cars.  In most cases the cars they drive have foreign registered plates because URA has issued them a Temporary Road License (TRL).  A TRL is a document usually given to foreigners intending to come into Uganda with their foreign registered vehicles or Ugandans working abroad with valid work permits. These in most cases come from South- Sudan and DRCongo. With the TRL, a person is granted a maximum of 90 days and once they elapse, they are supposed to return to their countries.  However, this is not the case. Some foreigners and the ba-summer violate the TRLs. They choose to stay and test their luck with expired TRLs which is an offense.  “If you have been granted a TRL you are not supposed to lend out your car or sell it to anyone here [Uganda] without permission. If you want to sell it, you have to notify the Commissioner Customs,” Godson Mwesigye, the Manager Enforcement operations said of the TRL violations.  With URA ’s continued vigilance, a number of culprits have been netted and had their cars impounded. The latest is a Mercedes- Benz GLE350d that was impounded in Adjumani.  According to the Customs Enforcement team in Elegu, the Benz had plates belonging to a Toyota.  “This means it had paid taxes in South-Sudan and crossed over to Uganda with un paid taxes. In order to avoid taxes, the owner was “clever” enough to change the plates belonging to a different car," explained a Customs officer.  The impounded Benz is currently parked at the URA offices in Elegu pending offence procedure. The penalty includes a fine of taxes amounting to USD 20,000(UGX 76,000,000).  Enforcement also revealed that the offence on violation of the TRLs starts by identifying the crime before one is penalized. Those who fail to fulfil their penalties, their cars get auctioned in the long run.  .@IBbossa, the URA Spokesperson noted that URA is expected to collect more revenue this financial year so continuous driving of non-authorized vehicles on the road affects the taxes URA collects for improved service delivery.  He also added that URA is committed to cracking the vice to ensure that every Ugandan pays their fair share of revenue.  Currently, a number of field operations are ongoing to net more culprits.  NB: * Tag your 'Mu-summer' friend.*  #URAEnforcementAlert #Customs101
